# Environment Configuration

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values:

```bash
# Server
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3000

# Database
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/puzzlechain
MONGODB_URI_TEST=mongodb://localhost:27017/puzzlechain-test

# JWT - CRITICAL: Generate strong random secrets (256-bit)
# Use: openssl rand -hex 32
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-key-here-min-32-chars
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=your-refresh-secret-key-here-min-32-chars
JWT_EXPIRE=7d
JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRE=30d

# Redis (optional - for rate limiting)
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379

# Client URL
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:5173

# Stripe Payment (required for production)
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...

# Internal API Key (for admin operations)
# Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
INTERNAL_API_KEY=

# Rate Limiting
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW=900000
RATE_LIMIT_MAX=100

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=info
```

## Generating Secure Secrets

```bash
# Generate 256-bit (32 byte) random hex string
openssl rand -hex 32

# Or use Node.js
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
```
